lished to all nodes. This allows bitcoin software to determine when a particular bitcoin amount has been spent, which is necessary in order to prevent double-spending in an environment without central oversight. Whereas a conventional ledger records the transfers of actual bills or promissory notes that exist apart from it, the block chain is the only place that bitcoins can be said to exist in the form of unspent outputs of transactions.","type":"paragraph"},{"id":"c3f33772ff2b00f2","text":"But this definition sucks - and is [[Bitcoin]] specific.","type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Blockchains"}